%N A290190 Minimum sum of mutual Manhattan distances of n distinct grid points in a cubic lattice.
%C A290190 Sum of mutual L1-distances of locations in a 3-dimensional n-town of optimum shape.
%C A290190 Conjecture: a(k^3) = A292045(k), i.e., fully populated cubes are optimal 3-dimensional n-towns. - _Hugo Pfoertner_, Jan 08 2026
%C A290190 The conjecture is false. Optimal 3-dimensional k^3-towns exist for k >= 4 with distance sums < A292045(k). For example, there are 64-towns (see linked illustration) with distance sum = 7539 < A292045(4) = 7680 and 125-towns with distance sum 36522 < A292045(5) = 37500. - _Hugo Pfoertner_, Jan 26 2026
